text:
Trying to set ViewPager’s height to be equaling the height of Recyclerview that’s in it. However, when I do override onMeasure method to get the height, the getMeasuredHeight is always 0.  Hence, heightMeasureSpec is always  0. And nothing gets displayed in the Viewpager.

```
        @Override
    protected void onMeasure(int widthMeasureSpec, int heightMeasureSpec) {

       if (mCurrentView == null) {
           super.onMeasure(widthMeasureSpec, heightMeasureSpec);
           return;
       }

       int height = 0;
       mCurrentView.measure(widthMeasureSpec, MeasureSpec.makeMeasureSpec(0, MeasureSpec.UNSPECIFIED));
       int h = mCurrentView.getMeasuredHeight();
       if (h &gt; height) {
           height = h;
       }

       heightMeasureSpec = MeasureSpec.makeMeasureSpec(height, MeasureSpec.EXACTLY);

        super.onMeasure(widthMeasureSpec, heightMeasureSpec);
    }
```
